# <center>install gromacs environment with conda</center>

## 1. create conda env of gromacs

    conda create -n gromacs

## 2. activate gromacs env

    conda activate gromacs

## 3. install gromacs with conda

    conda install gromacs=2023.4=nompi_cuda_h6303bc7_1

## 4. test the gromacs command line

    gmx

    gmx pdb2gmx -h

## 5. conda getting started

check conda env installed

    conda env list

activate conda env

    conda activate gromacs

start your work

    gmx
    gmx pdb2gmx -h  
    gmx help commands  

inthe end deactivate conda env

    conda deactivate
